👉 This is real SRE learning

🟢 LEVEL 1: Basic (understand metrics)
🎯 Goal: Learn what metrics exist

Go to:

http://localhost:9090

Try:

node_cpu_seconds_total
node_memory_MemTotal_bytes
node_filesystem_size_bytes
node_network_receive_bytes_total

👉 Learn:

Metric names
Labels (instance, job, mode)
🟡 LEVEL 2: Filtering & labels
🎯 Goal: Select correct data
node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}
node_filesystem_size_bytes{fstype="ext4"}
node_network_receive_bytes_total{device="eth0"}

👉 Learn:

Filtering using {label="value"}
Regex:
{fstype=~"ext.*|xfs"}
🔵 LEVEL 3: Rates (VERY IMPORTANT)

Counters need rate()

rate(node_cpu_seconds_total[5m])
rate(node_network_receive_bytes_total[5m])

👉 Learn:

Why counters increase
Convert to per-second values
🟣 LEVEL 4: Aggregation
🎯 Goal: Combine data
avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total[5m]))
sum(rate(node_network_receive_bytes_total[5m]))
avg by (instance)(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total[5m]))

👉 Learn:

sum, avg, by
🔴 LEVEL 5: Real SRE queries

Now build useful metrics 👇

🖥️ CPU usage %
100 * (1 - avg by (instance) (rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m])))
💾 Memory usage %
100 * (1 - node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes / node_memory_MemTotal_bytes)
💿 Disk usage %
100 * (1 - node_filesystem_avail_bytes / node_filesystem_size_bytes)
🌐 Network bandwidth
rate(node_network_receive_bytes_total[5m])
🧪 LEVEL 6: Create real problems

Install stress:

sudo apt install stress
🔥 CPU spike
stress --cpu 2 --timeout 60

👉 Watch CPU query increase

🧠 Memory spike
stress --vm 1 --vm-bytes 1G --timeout 60
💾 Disk usage
fallocate -l 1G testfile

👉 This step is critical

📊 LEVEL 7: Grafana practice

In Grafana:

Create panels for:

CPU %
Memory %
Disk %
Network

👉 Then:

Change time ranges
Use legends
Add thresholds
🚨 LEVEL 8: Alerts (real SRE skill)

Example:

- alert: HighCPU
  expr: 100 * (1 - avg by(instance)(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m]))) > 80
  for: 2m

👉 Practice:

Trigger it using stress
Observe firing
🧠 LEVEL 9: Advanced PromQL
🔹 Top usage
topk(5, node_filesystem_size_bytes)
🔹 Sorting
sort_desc(node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes)
🔹 Percentiles (advanced systems)
histogram_quantile(0.95, rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m]))
🔹 Predict future (very advanced)
predict_linear(node_filesystem_free_bytes[1h], 3600)
🔍 LEVEL 10: Debugging scenarios

Practice like this:

Scenario 1: CPU high
Check CPU query
Identify process
Scenario 2: Disk full
Use disk query
Find mount point
Scenario 3: Network spike
Check RX/TX
Identify traffic

